uturism's model of integrating art with politics and life, the murals of revolutionary Mexico and Nicaragua, 1960s American art, and the Slovenian art collective NSK's construction of a fictional political state in the 1990s. Aesthetic Revolutions and Twentieth-Century Avant-Garde Movements traces the common foundations and goals shared by these disparate arts communities and shows how their art worked towards effecting political and social change.Contributors. John E. Bowlt, Sascha Bru, David Craven, Aleš Erjavec, Tyrus Miller, Raymond Spiteri, Miško Šuvakovic   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aAestheticsxPolitical aspects. 0aAvant-garde (Aesthetics)xHistoryy20th century. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh1 aErjavec, Aleš, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraven, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErjavec, Aleš, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBowlt, John E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpiteri, Raymond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBru, Sascha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Tyrus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822375661zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822375661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822375661.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles